   "body" : "Given Issue #4124 (bitcoind as system service) and now that PR #4611 (init scripts and docs for Upstart and OpenRC) is merged, it would be nice to see some updates to the Debian packaging (in `contrib/debian`, right?) to properly install `bitcoind` as a system service.\n\nIt would also be nice to see better documentation on the Debian/Ubuntu package:\n- Where it lives (source and binary)\n- Better build instructions\n- etc\n\n(I've done a little bit of work in this area on my own, but am an Debian/Ubuntu newb. I'm definitely willing to help with testing and documentation.)\n\nReferences:\n- [Debian contrib directory](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/tree/master/contrib/debian)\n- [Bitcoin LaunchPad page](https://launchpad.net/~bitcoin/+archive/ubuntu/bitcoin)\n",
